title: Human blood set to 'soak' Vatican in protest inspired by Sinead O'Connor
description: Human blood is set to "soak" the Vatican in a protest inspired by the late singer Sinead O'Connor.

title: Former Harrods and Fulham FC owner Mohamed Al Fayed has died
description: Mohamed Al Fayed has died at the age of 94.

title: Under fire Spanish FA president issues new defence of 'mutual and consented' World Cup final kiss
description: Spanish FA president Luis Rubiales has issued a fresh defence after kissing a player on the lips following the Women's World Cup final.

title: Former Nazi guard, 98, charged with 3,330 counts of accessory to murder
description: A 98-year-old former Nazi concentration camp guard has been charged with being an accessory to murder.

title: Blink 182 postpone UK gigs as Travis Barker rushes home for 'urgent family matter'
description: Blink-182 has postponed gigs across the UK and Ireland as drummer Travis Barker rushed home to the US for an "urgent family matter".

title: Spanish men's football coach apologises for applauding Rubiales
description: The coach of the Spanish men's national football team, Luis de la Fuente, has apologised for applauding Luis Rubiales during the speech in which he refused to resign.

title: Fear, family and near-death experiences: 18 months as a Ukrainian refugee in the UK
description: Russia's invasion of Ukraine forced millions of people to flee their homes. Almost 170,000 of them have spent much of the last 18 months navigating new lives in the UK.

title: Briton killed in Ukraine 'paid ultimate price defending people he'd never met', says dad
description: The father of a British volunteer killed fighting in Ukraine has told Sky News he "paid the ultimate price for defending people he'd never met".

title: Eighteen suspects shot and killed in shootout with South African police
description: Eighteen suspects have been shot and killed during a shootout with South African police.

title: Irish town comes to standstill for funeral of siblings in fatal crash
description: The Irish town of Clonmel came to a standstill as a funeral was held for a brother and sister killed in a crash in Co Tipperary last week.

title: Drones give Ukraine's underdogs an advantage - but their daring raids won't end this war | Sean Bell
description: Ukraine might have thwarted Russian ambitions to subjugate the whole of the country, but it faces a herculean task if it is to expel Russian forces from occupied territories completely.

title: Moroccan tourists 'shot dead' after entering Algerian waters on jet ski
description: Two Moroccan tourists on jet skis have reportedly been shot dead after straying into Algerian waters.

title: Adieu e-scooters! Paris becomes first European capital to ban rental vehicles
description: A ban on self-service rental e-scooters has come into force in Paris after the people of the French capital city voted overwhelmingly against them.

title: Ukraine and grain likely to feature in Putin-Erdogan talks
description: Black Sea grain exports are likely to be discussed when Vladimir Putin meets Recep Tayyip Erdogan for talks on Monday.

title: 'Evil' but 'a people person': Saddam Hussein according to the soldier who guarded him
description: This year marks 20 years since the Iraq war and the capture of dictator Saddam Hussein.

title: Hundreds of flights cancelled as Typhoon Saola barrels towards Hong Kong
description: Hundreds of flights have been cancelled in Hong Kong and the neighbouring Chinese province of Guangdong ahead of the arrival of Typhoon Saola.

title: Three countries and far-right politician have Nobel Foundation ban reversed
description: Russia, Belarus and Iran have all been readmitted to the Nobel Foundation, after the organisation reversed its previous policy of banning them.

title: Legionnaires' disease has killed 16 people in Poland and been found on the asylum seeker barge - but what is it?
description: The bacteria that causes Legionnaires' disease has been found in Poland near the Ukrainian border and on the barge due to house asylum seekers in Dorset.

title: NASA reveals likely cause of new crater on the moon
description: NASA has found a new crater on the moon likely caused by the impact of a Russian spacecraft that crashed last month.

title: Aspirin 'could help cut diabetes risk in over-65s'
description: Taking aspirin every day could lower the type 2 diabetes risk among people over 65, a study suggests.

title: Fugitive stepmother of 10-year-old girl who was found dead urged to hand herself in by relative
description: A relative of Sara Sharif's stepmother has urged her to return to the UK and hand herself in to the police.
